      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHERIFF'S STAR (5) left himself with too much to do last start at Ipswich but did warm to make some inroads. Gets back but will wind up late. Leading contender. DANCING TILDA (1) has put together back-to-back placings, the latest when third over 1500m at Port Macquarie when he was in the firing line all the way. Strips rock-hard fit and will handle the conditions. Gets another good chance to break through. FOXY ARTIST (2) has been well supported throughout his career without breaking through, only managing fourth last start at Coffs Harbour. Blinkers go on to sharpen him up and is worth another chance. PRESSIPITATING (9) has had plenty of chances to break through but there are efforts littered through her form that can measure up. Keeping safe.",
